from command prompt with directory the same one as where decomp.f90 is installed (and probably f2py.py):

python2 -m numpy.f2py -c building_volume_frac.f90 -m building_volume_frac


python2 -m numpy.f2py -c building_volume_frac.f90 -fbounds-check -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,overflow -m building_volume_frac

python2 f2py_build.py

FORTRAN COMPILING: 
gfortran -ffree-line-length-none -ffixed-line-length-none   -fdefault-real-8 -fbounds-check -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,overflow -o shape_functions shape_functions.f90

COMPILING MULTIPLE FILES:
gfortran -c -o programA.o programA.f90
gfortran -c -o programB.o programB.f90
gfortran -c -o programC.o programC.f90
gfortran -o output mainprogram.f90 programA.o programB.o programC.o

HERE:
gfortran -ffree-line-length-none -ffixed-line-length-none -fdefault-real-8 space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1.o  space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1.f90

gfortran -o shape_functions shape_functions.f90 space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1

gfortran -ffree-line-length-none -ffixed-line-length-none   -fdefault-real-8 -fbounds-check -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,overflow -o shape_functions shape_functions.f90 space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1.o



Dont include programme main in space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1_w to produce a *.o file:

gfortran   -ffree-line-length-none -ffixed-line-length-none -c -fdefault-real-8 -o space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1_w.o  space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1_w.f90

gfortran -ffree-line-length-none -ffixed-line-length-none   -fdefault-real-8 -fbounds-check -ffpe-trap=invalid,zero,overflow -o shape_functions shape_functions.f90 space_filling_decomp_new_random_decide_v1_w.o

